name: Joey Chestnut
summary: Joey Chestnut, the reigning champion of the iconic Nathan's Famous Hot Dog Eating Contest, has been banned from the event for 2024. The ban stems from a sponsorship deal Chestnut secured with Impossible Foods, which violated Nathan's exclusivity agreement with Oscar Mayer. Chestnut has expressed disappointment over the ban, stating that he feels "gutted." Despite the ban, Chestnut will still participate in hot dog eating competitions, including an event at Fort Bliss in Texas on July 4th. His absence from Nathan's has led to speculation about who will win the contest, with Takamu Kobayashi, Chestnut's former rival, being among the favorites. The ban has also raised questions about Chestnut's dietary choices, with some wondering if his veganism contributed to the dispute with Nathan's.
